6. **Create an admin user**:

    ```bash
    php artisan make:model User -mcr
    ```

    This will create a User model, a migration file, and a controller.

    Next, add the following code to the migration file (`database/migrations/xxxx_xx_xx_xxxxxx_create_users_table.php`) to add the necessary fields:

    ```php
    use Illuminate\Database\Migrations\Migration;
    use Illuminate\Database\Schema\Blueprint;
    use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Schema;

    return new class extends Migration
    {
        public function up()
        {
            Schema::create('users', function (Blueprint $table) {
                $table->id();
                $table->string('name');
                $table->string('email')->unique();
                $table->timestamp('email_verified_at')->nullable();
                $table->string('password');
                $table->rememberToken();
                $table->timestamps();
            });
        }

        public function down()
        {
            Schema::dropIfExists('users');
        }
    };
    ```

    Run the migration:

    ```bash
    php artisan migrate
    ```

    Now, use the `filament:make:user` Artisan command to create an admin user:

    ```bash
    php artisan filament:make:user --admin
    ```

    You will be prompted to enter the email and password for the admin user.

7. **Run the development server**:

    ```bash
    php artisan serve
    ```

Now, you should be able to access Filament at `http://127.0.0.1:8000/filament`. Log in with the admin user you created to start building your admin panel.
